# Form Patterns

Read `docs/FORM_PATTERNS.md` before creating or editing any form.

## Critical rule

Never use `{...register()}` on custom wrappers (`FormInput`, `FormMultiInput`, `CalendarInput`, `MarkdownEditor`, `UserSearch`). They are not ref-forwarding; RHF state and UI desync, especially after `reset()` in drawers.

Use **`Controller`** with explicit `value`, `onChange`, `onBlur`:

```tsx
<Controller
  name="title"
  control={control}
  render={({ field }) => (
    <FormInput
      name={field.name}
      value={field.value}
      onChange={field.onChange}
      onBlur={field.onBlur}
      errorMessage={errors.title?.message}
    />
  )}
/>
```

Native `<input>`, `<textarea>`, `<select>` in JSX may use `register()`.

